The warning is in place from 1pm to 10 pm on Monday and covers parts of the Midlands and Northern Ireland. The Met Office has warned that there is a chance of homes and businesses becoming flooded and of buildings becoming damaged by lightning strikes. On Monday, heavy showers are expected in between outbreaks of sunshine in the UK, with BBC Weather warning of a fresh deluge after a damp end to the weekend. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...